Without the amendment, Mr Museveni would have been ineligible to contest in the 2006 elections having served for two terms from 1996.





Africa's longest serving leaders, (clockwise), Equatorial Guinea’s Teodoro Obiang, Cameroon's Paul Biya, Chadian Idriss Deby, Congo-Brazzaville's Denis Sassou Nguesso, Sudan's Omar Bashir, Eritrea's Isaias Afwerki, Eswatini's King Mswati III and Ugandan Yoweri Museveni.
